 I'll use the druid tunic as an example.  This is a COMPLETE but logical GUESS on the druid tunic.  Going off the same pattern we've seen on other pieces, lets take a look at the enchanter robe.<br>
<br>
AC15 +3dex +5cha +8int +10hp +20mana +2FR/CLD/MAG<br>
<br>
Broken down as 'petercorbin' did earlier with other pieces that would be:<br>
+8 to main stat<br>
+5 to secondary<br>
+3 to tertiary<br>
<br>
So I would guess for the druid tunic, substitue WIS for INT and STA for CHA.  DEX would remain as the third stat.  I imagine saves would remain the same and possibly mana as well, but +hp and AC would be different.  All in all not a bad piece especially for a mid 30s to mid 40s druid.  I may go after this myself to hopefully confirm it.<br>
<br>
Gilethan<br>
51st Druid<br>
